{"title":"Introducing Basic Cycle Co: A Modern Classic in Road Cycling","link":"https://theradavist.com/basic-cycle-co-classic-steel-road-frames/","date":1745409626000,"content":"<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://radavist-static-production.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/2025/04/Basic-Bicycle-Co-05.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://radavist-static-production.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/2025/04/Basic-Bicycle-Co-05.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://radavist-static-production.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/2025/04/Basic-Bicycle-Co-05.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://radavist-static-production.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/2025/04/Basic-Bicycle-Co-05.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p><em>The simple <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/riding-as-ceremony-a-vintage-road-bike-is-all-you-need/\" target=\"_blank\">rim brake road bike</a> is a thing of beauty and elegance in today’s world of internal routing and disc brakes. Basic Cycle Co is a new company out of Tacoma, Washington, offering just that…</em><span></span></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://radavist-static-production.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/2025/04/Basic-Bicycle-Co-01.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://radavist-static-production.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/2025/04/Basic-Bicycle-Co-01.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://radavist-static-production.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/2025/04/Basic-Bicycle-Co-01.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://radavist-static-production.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/2025/04/Basic-Bicycle-Co-01.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>Mechanical rim brake road bikes still have a place in today’s cycling world. The brand’s frames are built in the USA of Columbus Life and Zona tubing; paired with a Whisky RD+ carbon fork and designed for mid-reach brakes means accommodation of up to 35c tires, or up to 28c with fenders. The result is a lightweight setup ready to handle any “road” you find.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://radavist-static-production.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/2025/04/Basic-Bicycle-Co-02.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://radavist-static-production.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/2025/04/Basic-Bicycle-Co-02.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://radavist-static-production.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/2025/04/Basic-Bicycle-Co-02.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://radavist-static-production.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/2025/04/Basic-Bicycle-Co-02.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://radavist-static-production.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/2025/04/Basic-Bicycle-Co-03.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://radavist-static-production.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/2025/04/Basic-Bicycle-Co-03.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://radavist-static-production.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/2025/04/Basic-Bicycle-Co-03.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://radavist-static-production.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/2025/04/Basic-Bicycle-Co-03.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>The brand has kept things simple when it comes to parts compatibility. Each frame features a BSA threaded bottom bracket, 1-1/8” headset, 27.2mm seat post, mechanical cable stops, and a 132.5mm rear hub spacing that accommodates a wide range of road, cyclocross, or classic MTB hubs. Basic hopes riders will mix the old and new—combining beloved, functional parts with thoughtful modern touches to build something uniquely their own.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://radavist-static-production.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/2025/04/Basic-Bicycle-Co-04.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://radavist-static-production.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/2025/04/Basic-Bicycle-Co-04.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://radavist-static-production.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/2025/04/Basic-Bicycle-Co-04.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://radavist-static-production.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/2025/04/Basic-Bicycle-Co-04.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>Basic road frames and forks are available now in three colors and sizes 49, 52, 55, and 58. Choose from Continental Black Cerakote frame with raw carbon fork for $1999, or Meissen Blue/Metallic Maroon with matching painted fork for $2350.</p>\n<p>Roll on over to <a href=\"https://www.basiccycle.co/road-bike\" target=\"_blank\">basiccycle.co</a> for more.</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/basic-cycle-co-classic-steel-road-frames/\">Introducing Basic Cycle Co: A Modern Classic in Road Cycling</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theradavist.com\">The Radavist</a>.</p>","author":"John Watson","siteTitle":"The Radavist","siteHash":"96eb481d8084f04a4602bac57874ba717baf56b758f45547b5caf2312da766ef","entryHash":"fbcd0e1a5dba41ae106330b986c8f3bd3af5972012b3bf4f332a0af508d60728","category":"Cycling"}